      <tr><td  class="contentstyle10089" >
        <div id='vsb_content' >
           <P>From August 24 to 25, the International Symposium on Education of High Level Engineers held grandly in Shanghai Jiao Tong University. There are many well-known professors attending the opening ceremony, such as academician J.David EMBURY, academician Yves BRECHET, professor David G. EVANS, academician Du Youwei, academician Ruan Xueyu, professor Wang Hong and deputy president Huang Zhen. More than 100 experts and scholars from more than 20 famous domestic and overseas universities, research institutions and more than 10 well-known enterprises took part in the symposium.</P>
<P><IMG alt="" src="/_mediafile/icae/2011/09/09/ly1bmp8wt2.jpg" width="599" height="399"></P>
<P>With the approval of Ministry of Education, the symposium was sponsored by SJTU, organized by school of Materials Science and Engineering (SMSE), co-organized by association ＂A Better World via Education＂(PMME), Office of Undergraduate Education and Graduate School. The two-day symposium focused on＂Excellent Engineering Education and Training Scheme＂. The experts and scholars discussed many topics, such as education modes of materials science and engineering in China and the West, collaboration between universities and industrial enterprises, developing new mechanisms of international cooperation in current global situation. Academicians and experts from France, Canada, Britain and China, with experts from domestic and overseas universities, business representatives from Air Liquide Group (France), Baoshan Iron &amp; Steel Co., Ltd, GM (China) Investment Co., Ltd and Baotou National Research Institute of Rare Earths and etc, made 14 invited presentations on symposium topics.</P>
<P><IMG title="Professor Huang Zhen" alt="" src="/_mediafile/icae/2011/09/09/qbiki98wt3.jpg" width="200" height="155" style="float: left;margin-right: 2px">In the opening ceremony, deputy president Huang Zhen extended his warm welcome to the guests. He said, as one of the first universities to implement the "Excellent Engineer Education and Training Scheme", SJTU actively cooperated with well-known enterprises to set up new-style teaching system based on our powerful engineering activities. Guided by new target system of talent cultivation, many new educational measures were carried out in our university, including reform of teaching methods, joint education between colleges and enterprises, etc. These measures allowed us to improve the quality of our engineering students, their skills in innovation and their practical abilities. Moreover, there were still a lot of urgent problems to be solved. These issued include establishing mechanisms to maximize the benefits to both the universities and industrial enterprises. How to strengthen the skills of our students related to innovation? How to expand the flexibility of engineering education and increase the level of internationalization? He sincerely hoped this symposium contribute new ideas and innovative suggestions to improve our educational offerings and collaboration with industry.</P>
<DIV sizcache="4" sizset="73" style="clear: both">
<P><IMG title="David Embury" alt="" src="/_mediafile/icae/2011/09/09/awyew48wt4.jpg" width="163" height="167" style="float: right;margin-left: 2px">Professor J.David EMBURY from McMaster University, a member of US Academy of Sciences &amp; FRSC, gave a speech that the International Symposium is a good platform for education in China. The symposium focused on＂Excellent Engineering Education and Training Scheme＂, played an important role on Chinese economic growth and development, and had a great influence on education in other countries.</P>
<DIV sizcache="4" sizset="73" style="clear: both">
<P><IMG title="Wu Yixiong" alt="" src="/_mediafile/icae/2011/09/09/lhf52x8wt5.jpg" width="200" height="163" style="float: left;margin-left: 2px">The objective of the first session of this symposium was ＂Education Mode of International Material Engineering＂. The session was held by Professor Wu Yixiong, the dean of school of Materials Science and Engineering.</P>
<DIV sizcache="4" sizset="73" style="clear: both">
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P><IMG title="Wang Hong" alt="" src="/_mediafile/icae/2011/09/09/0npxe98wt6.jpg" width="200" height="182" style="float: right;margin-left: 2px"> Professor Wang Hong, president of Shanghai University of Engineering Science, representative of Ministry of Education, gave the first talk. She said, ＂A plan for Education of High Level Engineers＂ was of important demonstrative and instructive effects on issues in higher education such as reforming and renovating engineering talents training mode, establishing new mechanism for joint talents training by universities and industries, cultivating students' practical skills, design abilities and creativity in engineering.＂The Plan＂take fully into account the diverse industry sectors and various demands for engineering talents; it attaches great importance to the demands for talents put forward by national industrial restructuring and invigoration plan as well as developing strategic emerging industries. According to general standard and professional standard, ＂The Plan＂aims to train reserve engineers of bachelor, master and PhD in various methods through on campus study and industry learning.＂The Plan＂gives priority to six fields, namely: Establishing outstanding engineer training mode; Seting up training system for practical ability and creativity, providing the platform; Building high ranks of engineering teachers; Pushing forward internationalization of engineering education; Seting training standard and appraisal system for engineering talents; Management system innovation. Strategic thinking and exploration would be made in areas like clarifying engineers training responsibilities, setting standards and its accomplishment matrix, developing perfect industry learning program, enhance engineering background of teachers, introducing and implementing international accreditation, expanding cooperation with multi-national enterprises so as to better facilitate reform and innovation of engineering education, upgrade overall quality of engineering education and talents training in China. We strove to build up modern higher engineering education system with Chinese characteristics and of advanced world level, and propel China from a country with large number of students in engineering education to a country strong in engineering education.</P>
<DIV sizcache="4" sizset="73" style="clear: both">
<P>Professor J.David EMBURY from McMaster University, a member of US Academy of Sciences &amp; FRSC, illustrated how various educational programs have developed and how to educate students to develop into technological leaders. Emphasis would be given both to developing an individual knowledge base and the ability to integrate into group activities to achieve complex engineering objectives.</P>
<P><IMG title="Yves Brechet" alt="" src="/_mediafile/icae/2011/09/09/3pipjz8wt7.jpg" width="200" height="183" style="float: left;margin-right: 2px">Professor Yves BRECHET from INP-Grenoble, a member of the French Academy of Science and the European Academy of Science, introduced the unique French system of high level engineering schools called ＂Grandes Ecoles＂.</P>
<DIV sizcache="4" sizset="73" style="clear: both">
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P><IMG title="David Evans" alt="" src="/_mediafile/icae/2011/09/09/4j87nu8wt8.jpg" width="200" height="205" style="float: left;margin-right: 2px"></P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Professor David G.EVANS from Beijing University of Chemical Technology, a fellow of the Royal Society of Chemistry, said that Mobility of researchers was important in strengthening international research cooperation.</P>
<DIV sizcache="4" sizset="73" style="clear: both">
<P>The objective of the second session of this symposium was ＂The Relation of Education to Industrial Needs＂. The session was chaired by Professor ZHANG Kui from Université de Reims (France), the leadership of PMME.</P>
<P>Professor Du Youwei from Nanjing University, a member of Chinese Academy of Sciences, said that talents were the cornerstone of enterprise prosperity. First-class talents could produce first-class products, which enabled enterprises to be invincible in the intensely competitive market.</P>
<P sizcache="4" sizset="73">Mr. Philippe MERINO from Air Liquide Group, the director of technology department, said that a good understanding of how a company works was absolutely paramount. One interesting feature that had been notices was the much beneficial role played by <A name="OLE_LINK36">long internships in companies</A>: young engineers prove themselves much more fit to company work and improve technology ability.</P>
<P>Mr. Huang Jiaohong from Baotou Research Institute of Rare Earth, the deputy chief engineer, said that engineering work was different with research work. Engineers worked at enterprise and workshop whose duty mostly was providing technical guidelines and advices for a special production task. Engineering technology work was the actually work which should combine with the economic benefit of enterprises, so it was not premised to fail.</P>
<P>Mr. Zhang Yongjie from Baoshan Iron &amp; Steel Co., Ltd, the assistant director of Research Institute (R&amp;D Center), said that Baosteel and Shanghai Jiao Tong University went together for high-level engineering education in 2004. For Students, with close advising and mentoring from university and corporate partner, association and interaction with a highly selective group from the best technical universities, they got the well education. For SJTU, enhance knowledge transfer between academia and industry，establish strategic linkages with Baosteel. For Baosteel, gain visibility among students and choice to get the best engineers. It was show that the cooperation was success. The education and training for high-level engineers was one of the most important ways for Baosteel.</P>
<P>The objective of the third session of this symposium was ＂Defining New Approaches and New Skills＂. The session was chaired by Professor Jin Xuejun, the associate dean of school of Materials Science and Engineering.</P>
<P>Professor ZHANG Kui from Université de Reims, gave a report that we should be careful about what to learn from the west, how to learn, how to adapt and improve under Chinese circumstances, in order to educate engineers of high levels in the future.&nbsp;</P>
<P>Professor Luo Zhen from school of Materials Science and Engineering in Tianjin University, said that it was important to establish a student training system. He also illustrated how to transform traditional education into quality education, how to transform major education into specialized fields, how to transform university education into Industry-University cooperation education, how to transform teach-oriented education into study-oriented education.</P>
<P>Doctor Marc FRY from Cambridge Granta Design Ltd, the director of education department, introduced some of the ways that he did this in his teaching in Cambridge University. It was important to get across to students both the history of our subject and its linking role in modern engineering practice.&nbsp;</P>
<P>Doctor John Du from GM (China) Investment Co., Ltd, the director of China Science Laboratory, introduced the top 10 skills students need to be a good engineer/researcher at a technology-orientated company.</P>
<P>Professor Wang Min from school of Materials Science and Engineering in SJTU, gave a report. She said, according to positioning and training objectives of excellent engineers in materials science and engineering field, its education and training scheme was designed in top-level. The emphasis and characteristics of the scheme were focused on the following: strengthening the basis of professional education, highlighting engineering quality cultivation and various teaching mode. The training plan orchestrated the project knowledge, engineering practice, engineering training and engineering research and development in university and in company, throughout the excellent engineers training of "ability chain". In addition, the Engineering Education Steering Committee, undergraduate tutorial system, and class committee on duty by turns etc. had established. It would enhance the quality and ability of the comprehensive training of excellent engineers.</P>
<P>As an important reform event, ＂A plan for Education of High Level Engineers＂ by Ministry of Education thoroughly applied＂ National education reform and development of long-term planning programs (2010-2020) ＂ and ＂National talent development of long-term planning programs (2010-2020) ＂. ＂The Plan＂ was also to improve our country from a major industrial education country to a world industrial education power. It aimed to train various high-level engineers, who had design abilities and creativity in engineering, match the social economic development needs.</P>
<P>＂The Plan＂ was good for our country to take a new road to industrialization, construct an innovative country, and implementing the strategy to be a world talent power. It also had demonstrative and instructive effects on advancing higher education to train talents who matched the social needs, and improving the quality of education of high-level engineers.</P>
<P>Since 2010, Ministry of Education had launched and improved "A plan for Education of High Level Engineers". Through ＂The Plan＂, various high-level engineers would be trained in next 10 years. Up to June, 2011, Ministry of Education had allowed 61 universities to carry out the plan, including Tsinghua University and Shanghai Jiao Tong University. "How to train real high-level engineers?" became a research topic in domestic and overseas universities. Through the international symposium, we learned to draw in the experience of education of high level engineers in west. In order to improve the quality of education of high level engineers, this symposium was good for us to improve education mode, teaching methods, collaboration between universities and industrial enterprises.</P></DIV></DIV></DIV></DIV></DIV></DIV>
</div>
